author: WAFB Staff
title: POSTGAME COVERAGE: LSU players talk about 35-28 victory over Flo
text:
BATON ROUGE, LA (WAFB) - If viewing this story on a mobile device or in an email, click the link for postgame coverage, including LSU head coach Les Miles' news conference - http://shout.lt/bf54r , LSU player interviews - http://shout.lt/bf54M
No. 6 LSU used a fake field goal to get past No. 8 Florida, 35-28 and remain unbeaten. The Tigers hand the Gators their first lost of the season.
Sophomore running back Leonard Fournette ran for 180 yards and two touchdowns.
Sophomore quarterback Brandon Harris threw 13 of 19 passes for 202 yards, including two touchdowns passes to Dupre.
Junior kicker Trent Domingue had a 16-yard touchdown run after a fake field goal.
Sophomore wide receiver Malachi Dupre had 115 receiving yards, catching two touchdowns from Harris.
Senior linebacker Deion Jones had 10 tackles, 1 sack and 2.5 tackles for loss.
Junior defense end Lewis Neal had 10 tackles, 3 sacks, and 3.5 tackles for loss.
